B%20lawsuits%20against%20his%20administration.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20memo%20says%20that%20firms%20affiliated%20with%20the%20suits%20can%20be%20targeted%20for%20punitive%20executive%20actions.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ETrump%20has%20recently%20escalated%20his%20attacks%20on%20Big%20Law%2C%20drawing%20concern%20from%20legal%20scholars.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EPresident%20Donald%20Trump%20on%20Friday%20continued%20his%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-memo-orders-big-law-firms-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eescalating%20attacks%20on%20Big%20Law%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20this%20time%20with%20a%20directive%20to%20Attorney%20General%20Pam%20Bondi%3A%20flag%20the%20law%20firms%20affiliated%20with%20%26quot%3Bfrivolous%26quot%3B%20lawsuits%20against%20his%20administration%20so%20they%20can%20be%20targeted%20for%20executive%20actions%2C%20like%20having%20their%20security%20clearances%20revoked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERecently%2C%20the%20Trump%20administration%20has%20followed%20a%20similar%20playbook%20in%20targeting%20law%20firms%20affiliated%20with%20his%20political%20opponents%20and%20those%20who%20participated%20in%20investigations%20against%20him.%20Since%20February%2025%2C%20the%20president%20has%20ordered%20the%20revocation%20of%20security%20clearances%20for%20employees%20at%20Paul%20Weiss%2C%20Perkins%20Coie%2C%20and%20Covington%20%26amp%3B%20Burling.%20He%20also%20ordered%20a%20review%20of%20their%20government%20contracts%2C%20a%20major%20source%20of%20revenue%20for%20the%20firms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Thursday%2C%20Trump%20announced%20he%20planned%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpaul-weiss-trump-executive-order-agreement-language-dei-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewithdraw%20his%20executive%20order%3C%2Fa%3E%20targeting%20Paul%20Weiss%20after%20the%20law%20firm%20agreed%20that%20it%20%26quot%3Bwill%20not%20adopt%2C%20use%2C%20or%20pursue%20any%20DEI%20policies%26quot%3B%20and%20promised%20%2440%20million%20in%20pro%20bono%20legal%20services.%20On%20Friday%2C%20he%20signed%20a%20new%20executive%20order%20reversing%20his%20March%2014%2C%202025%2C%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPracticing%20lawyers%20and%20legal%20scholars%20alike%20have%20criticized%20the%20Trump%20administration's%20moves%20against%20the%20industry.%20On%20Thursday%2C%20a%20Skadden%20associate%2C%20Rachel%20Cohen%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fskadden-lawyer-resigns-firms-response-to-trump-paul-weiss-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epublicly%20announced%20her%20resignation%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20lamented%20that%20the%20legal%20profession%20was%20not%20doing%20enough%20to%20stand%20up%20against%20Trump's%20attacks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTrump%20pushes%20the%20limits%20of%20everything%3A%20the%20legal%20boundaries%2C%20picking%20fights%20with%20massive%20law%20firms%2C%20he's%20calling%20for%20the%20impeachment%20of%20federal%20judges%2C%26quot%3B%20Neama%20Rahmani%2C%20a%20former%20federal%20prosecutor%20and%20current%20trial%20lawyer%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BSo%20look%2C%20say%20what%20you%20want%20about%20him%2C%20but%20he%20seems%20to%20be%20winning%20%E2%80%94%20or%20at%20least%20putting%20a%20lot%20of%20pressure%20on%20folks%20throughout%20the%20legal%20industry%20to%20capitulate%20and%20bend%20to%20his%20will.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERepresentatives%20for%20the%20White%20House%20and%20attorney%20general's%20office%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lengthy%20memo%20sent%20to%20Bondi%20on%20Friday%2C%20titled%20%26quot%3BPreventing%20Abuses%20of%20the%20Legal%20System%20and%20the%20Federal%20Court%2C%26quot%3B%20reads%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3ELawyers%20and%20law%20firms%20that%20engage%20in%20actions%20that%20violate%20the%20laws%20of%20the%20United%20States%20or%20rules%20governing%20attorney%20conduct%20must%20be%20efficiently%20and%20effectively%20held%20accountable.%20Accountability%20is%20especially%20important%20when%20misconduct%20by%20lawyers%20and%20law%20firms%20threatens%20our%20national%20security%2C%20homeland%20security%2C%20public%20safety%2C%20or%20election%20integrity.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ERecent%20examples%20of%20grossly%20unethical%20misconduct%20are%20far%20too%20common.%20For%20instance%2C%20in%202016%2C%20Marc%20Elias%2C%20founder%20and%20chair%20of%20Elias%20Law%20Group%20LLP%2C%20was%20deeply%20involved%20in%20the%20creation%20of%20a%20false%20%26quot%3Bdossier%26quot%3B%20by%20a%20foreign%20national%20designed%20to%20provide%20a%20fraudulent%20basis%20for%20Federal%20law%20enforcement%20to%20investigate%20a%20Presidential%20candidate%20in%20order%20to%20alter%20the%20outcome%20of%20the%20Presidential%20election.%20Elias%20also%20intentionally%20sought%20to%20conceal%20the%20role%20of%20his%20client%20%E2%80%94%20failed%20Presidential%20candidate%20Hillary%20Clinton%20%E2%80%94%20in%20the%20dossier.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThe%20immigration%20system%20%E2%80%94%20where%20rampant%20fraud%20and%20meritless%20claims%20have%20supplanted%20the%20constitutional%20and%20lawful%20bases%20upon%20which%20the%20President%20exercises%20core%20powers%20under%20Article%20II%20of%20the%20United%20States%20Constitution%20%E2%80%94%20is%20likewise%20replete%20with%20examples%20of%20unscrupulous%20behavior%20by%20attorneys%20and%20law%20firms.%20For%20instance%2C%20the%20immigration%20bar%2C%20and%20powerful%20Big%20Law%20pro%20bono%20practices%2C%20frequently%20coach%20clients%20to%20conceal%20their%20past%20or%20lie%20about%20their%20circumstances%20when%20asserting%20their%20asylum%20claims%2C%20all%20in%20an%20attempt%20to%20circumvent%20immigration%20policies%20enacted%20to%20protect%20our%20national%20security%20and%20deceive%20the%20immigration%20authorities%20and%20courts%20into%20granting%20them%20undeserved%20relief.%20Gathering%20the%20necessary%20information%20to%20refute%20these%20fraudulent%20claims%20imposes%20an%20enormous%20burden%20on%20the%20Federal%20Government.%20And%20this%20fraud%20in%20turn%20undermines%20the%20integrity%20of%20our%20immigration%20laws%20and%20the%20legal%20profession%20more%20broadly%20%E2%80%94%20to%20say%20nothing%20of%20the%20undeniable%2C%20tragic%20consequences%20of%20the%20resulting%20mass%20illegal%20immigration%2C%20whether%20in%20terms%20of%20heinous%20crimes%20against%20innocent%20victims%20like%20Laken%20Riley%2C%20Jocelyn%20Nungaray%2C%20or%20Rachel%20Morin%2C%20or%20the%20enormous%20drain%20on%20taxpayer%20resources%20intended%20for%20Americans.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EFederal%20Rule%20of%20Civil%20Procedure%2011%20prohibits%20attorneys%20from%20engaging%20in%20certain%20unethical%20conduct%20in%20Federal%20courts.%20Attorneys%20must%20not%20present%20legal%20filings%20%26quot%3Bfor%20improper%20purpose%5Bs%5D%2C%26quot%3B%20including%20%26quot%3Bto%20harass%2C%20cause%20unnecessary%20delay%2C%20or%20needlessly%20increase%20the%20cost%20of%20litigation.%26quot%3B%20FRCP%2011(b)(1).%20Attorneys%20must%20ensure%20that%20legal%20arguments%20are%20%26quot%3Bwarranted%20by%20existing%20law%20or%20by%20a%20nonfrivolous%20argument%20for%20extending%2C%20modifying%2C%20or%20reversing%20existing%20law%20or%20for%20establishing%20new%20law.%26quot%3B%20FRCP%2011(b)(2).%20And%20attorneys%20must%20ensure%20that%20their%20statements%20about%20facts%20are%20%26quot%3Breasonably%20based%26quot%3B%20on%20evidentiary%20support%2C%20or%20a%20belief%20that%20such%20evidence%20actually%20exists.%20FRCP%2011(b)(3)-(b)(4).%20When%20these%20commands%20are%20violated%2C%20opposing%20parties%20are%20authorized%20to%20file%20a%20motion%20for%20sanctions.%20FRCP%2011(c).%20The%20text%20of%20the%20rule%20specifically%20addresses%20and%20provides%20for%20sanctions%20for%20attorneys%20and%20their%20firms%20as%20well%20as%20for%20recalcitrant%20parties%20given%20the%20solemn%20obligation%20that%20attorneys%20have%20to%20respect%20the%20rule%20of%20law%20and%20uphold%20our%20Nation's%20legal%20system%20with%20integrity.%20Furthermore%2C%20Rule%203.1%20of%20the%20Model%20Rules%20of%20Professional%20Conduct%20provides%20that%2C%20%26quot%3BA%20lawyer%20shall%20not%20bring%20or%20defend%20a%20proceeding%2C%20or%20assert%20or%20controvert%20an%20issue%20therein%2C%20unless%20there%20is%20a%20basis%20in%20law%20and%20fact%20for%20doing%20so%20that%20is%20not%20frivolous%2C%20which%20includes%20a%20good%20faith%20argument%20for%20an%20extension%2C%20modification%20or%20reversal%20of%20existing%20law.%26quot%3B%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EUnfortunately%2C%20far%20too%20many%20attorneys%20and%20law%20firms%20have%20long%20ignored%20these%20requirements%20when%20litigating%20against%20the%20Federal%20Government%20or%20in%20pursuing%20baseless%20partisan%20attacks.%20To%20address%20these%20concerns%2C%20I%20hereby%20direct%20the%20Attorney%20General%20to%20seek%20sanctions%20against%20attorneys%20and%20law%20firms%20who%20engage%20in%20frivolous%2C%20unreasonable%2C%20and%20vexatious%20litigation%20against%20the%20United%20States%20or%20in%20matters%20before%20executive%20departments%20and%20agencies%20of%20the%20United%20States.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EI%20further%20direct%20the%20Attorney%20General%20and%20the%20Secretary%20of%20Homeland%20Security%20to%20prioritize%20enforcement%20of%20their%20respective%20regulations%20governing%20attorney%20conduct%20and%20discipline.%20%3Cem%3ESee%2C%20e.g.%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%208%20C.F.R.%20292.1%20%3Cem%3Eet%20seq.%3C%2Fem%3E%3B%208%20C.F.R.%201003.101%20%3Cem%3Eet%20seq.%3C%2Fem%3E%3B%208%20C.F.R.%201292.19.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EI%20further%20direct%20the%20Attorney%20General%20to%20take%20all%20appropriate%20action%20to%20refer%20for%20disciplinary%20action%20any%20attorney%20whose%20conduct%20in%20Federal%20court%20or%20before%20any%20component%20of%20the%20Federal%20Government%20appears%20to%20violate%20professional%20conduct%20rules%2C%20including%20rules%20governing%20meritorious%20claims%20and%20contentions%2C%20and%20particularly%20in%20cases%20that%20implicate%20national%20security%2C%20homeland%20security%2C%20public%20safety%2C%20or%20election%20integrity.%20In%20complying%20with%20this%20directive%2C%20the%20Attorney%20General%20shall%20consider%20the%20ethical%20duties%20that%20law%20partners%20have%20when%20supervising%20junior%20attorneys%2C%20including%20imputing%20the%20ethical%20misconduct%20of%20junior%20attorneys%20to%20partners%20or%20the%20law%20firm%20when%20appropriate.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EI%20further%20direct%20that%2C%20when%20the%20Attorney%20General%20determines%20that%20conduct%20by%20an%20attorney%20or%20law%20firm%20in%20litigation%20against%20the%20Federal%20Government%20warrants%20seeking%20sanctions%20or%20other%20disciplinary%20action%2C%20the%20Attorney%20General%20shall%2C%20in%20consultation%20with%20any%20relevant%20senior%20executive%20official%2C%20recommend%20to%20the%20President%2C%20through%20the%20Assistant%20to%20the%20President%20for%20Domestic%20Policy%2C%20additional%20steps%20that%20may%20be%20taken%2C%20including%20reassessment%20of%20security%20clearances%20held%20by%20the%20attorney%20or%20termination%20of%20any%20Federal%20contract%20for%20which%20the%20relevant%20attorney%20or%20law%20firm%20has%20been%20hired%20to%20perform%20services.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EI%20further%20direct%20the%20Attorney%20General%2C%20in%20consultation%20with%20any%20relevant%20senior%20executive%20official%2C%20to%20review%20conduct%20by%20attorneys%20or%20their%20law%20firms%20in%20litigation%20against%20the%20Federal%20Government%20over%20the%20last%208%20years.%20If%20the%20Attorney%20General%20identifies%20misconduct%20that%20may%20warrant%20additional%20action%2C%20such%20as%20filing%20frivolous%20litigation%20or%20engaging%20in%20fraudulent%20practices%2C%20the%20Attorney%20General%20is%20directed%20to%20recommend%20to%20the%20President%2C%20through%20the%20Assistant%20to%20the%20President%20for%20Domestic%20Policy%2C%20additional%20steps%20that%20may%20be%20taken%2C%20including%20reassessment%20of%20security%20clearances%20held%20by%20the%20attorney%2C%20termination%20of%20any%20contract%20for%20which%20the%20relevant%20attorney%20or%20law%20firm%20has%20been%20hired%20to%20perform%20services%2C%20or%20any%20other%20appropriate%20actions.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ELaw%20firms%20and%20individual%20attorneys%20have%20a%20great%20power%2C%20and%20obligation%2C%20to%20serve%20the%20rule%20of%20law%2C%20justice%2C%20and%20order.%20The%20Attorney%20General%2C%20alongside%20the%20Counsel%20to%20the%20President%2C%20shall%20report%20to%20the%20President%20periodically%20on%20improvements%20by%20firms%20to%20capture%20this%20hopeful%20vision.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-attorney-general-memo-identify-target-law-firms-2025-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1742617118000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67de2cfc63d72727e197fee6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-attorney-general-memo-identify-target-law-firms-2025-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22President%20Donald%20Trump%20in%20a%20memo%20told%20AG%20Pam%20Bondi%20to%20report%20%26quot%3Bfrivolous%26quot%3B%20lawsuits%20against%20his%20administration.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ktangalakislippert%40businessinsider.com%20(Katherine%20Tangalakis-Lippert%2CKatherine%20Li)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A316%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-attorney-general-memo-identify-target-law-firms-2025-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22IPL%202025%E2%80%99s%20star%20attraction%3A%20The%20battles%20within%20battles%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1742616897000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-119328842%2Cimgsize-