%20alleging%20that%20the%20Trump%20administration%20unlawfully%20shut%20down%20the%20news%20organisation.%20The%20lawsuit%20claims%20that%20this%20action%20deprived%20many%20regions%20of%20an%20important%20source%20of%20objective%20news%2C%20with%20the%20closure%20attributed%20to%20political%20bias%20allegations.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20World%20Desk%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fobjective-news-is-gone-from-world-voice-of-america-accuses-trump-administration-of-unlawfully-shutting-it-down%2Farticleshow%2F119326434.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia-indiatimes-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fobjective-news-is-gone-from-world-voice-of-america-accuses-trump-administration-of-unlawfully-shutting-it-down%2Famp_articleshow%2F119326434.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fobjective-news-is-gone-from-world-voice-of-america-accuses-trump-administration-of-unlawfully-shutting-it-down%2Famp_articleshow%2F119326434.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22US%20Revokes%20Temporary%20Status%20Of%205%20Lakh%20Migrants%2C%20To%20Face%20Deportation%20Soon%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20Department%20of%20Homeland%20Security%20said%20Friday%20that%20it%20will%20revoke%20legal%20protections%20for%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20Cubans%2C%20Haitians%2C%20Nicaraguans%20and%20Venezuelans%2C%20setting%20them%20up%20for%20potential%20deportation%20in%20about%20a%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20order%20applies%20to%20about%205%2C32%2C000%20people%20from%20the%20four%20countries%20who%20came%20to%20the%20United%20States%20since%20October%202022.%20They%20arrived%20with%20financial%20sponsors%20and%20were%20given%20two-year%20permits%20to%20live%20and%20work%20in%20the%20US%20Homeland%20Security%20Secretary%20Kristi%20Noem%20said%20they%20will%20lose%20their%20legal%20status%20on%20April%2024%2C%20or%2030%20days%20after%20the%20publication%20of%20the%20notice%20in%20the%20Federal%20Register.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20policy%20impacts%20people%20who%20are%20already%20in%20the%20US%20and%20who%20came%20under%20the%20humanitarian%20parole%20program.%20It%20follows%20an%20earlier%20Trump%20administration%20decision%20to%20end%20what%20it%20called%20the%20%26quot%3Bbroad%20abuse%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20humanitarian%20parole%2C%20a%20long-standing%20legal%20tool%20presidents%20have%20used%20to%20allow%20people%20from%20countries%20where%20there's%20war%20or%20political%20instability%20to%20enter%20and%20temporarily%20live%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20his%20campaign%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20promised%20to%20deport%20millions%20of%20people%20who%20are%20in%20the%20US%20illegally%2C%20and%20as%20president%20he%20has%20been%20also%20ending%20legal%20pathways%20for%20immigrants%20to%20come%20to%20the%20US%20and%20to%20stay.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDHS%20said%20parolees%20without%20a%20lawful%20basis%20to%20stay%20in%20the%20US%20%26quot%3Bmust%20depart%26quot%3B%20before%20their%20parole%20termination%20date.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BParole%20is%20inherently%20temporary%2C%20and%20parole%20alone%20is%20not%20an%20underlying%20basis%20for%20obtaining%20any%20immigration%20status%2C%26quot%3B%20DHS%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBefore%20the%20new%20order%2C%20the%20beneficiaries%20of%20the%20program%20could%20stay%20in%20the%20U.S.%20until%20their%20parole%20expires%2C%20although%20the%20administration%20had%20stopped%20processing%20their%20applications%20for%20asylum%2C%20visas%20and%20other%20requests%20that%20might%20allow%20them%20to%20remain%20longer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20administration%20decision%20has%20already%20been%20challenged%20in%20federal%20courts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20group%20of%20American%20citizens%20and%20immigrants%20sued%20the%20Trump%20administration%20for%20ending%20humanitarian%20parole%20and%20are%20seeking%20to%20reinstate%20the%20programs%20for%20the%20four%20nationalities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELawyers%20and%20activists%20raised%20their%20voices%20to%20denounce%20the%20government's%20decision.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFriday's%20action%20is%20%26quot%3Bgoing%20to%20cause%20needless%20chaos%20and%20heartbreak%20for%20families%20and%20communities%20across%20the%20country%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Karen%20Tumlin%2C%20founder%20and%20director%20of%20Justice%20Action%20Center%2C%20one%20of%20the%20organizations%20that%20filed%20the%20lawsuit%20at%20the%20end%20of%20February.%20She%20called%20it%20%26quot%3Breckless%2C%20cruel%20and%20counterproductive.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Biden%20administration%20allowed%20up%20to%2030%2C000%20people%20a%20month%20from%20the%20four%20countries%20to%20come%20to%20the%20United%20States%20for%20two%20years%20with%20eligibility%20to%20work.%20It%20persuaded%20Mexico%20to%20take%20back%20the%20same%20number%20from%20those%20countries%20because%20the%20US%20could%20deport%20few%2C%20if%20any%2C%20to%20their%20homes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECuba%20generally%20accepted%20about%20one%20deportation%20flight%20a%20month%2C%20while%20Venezuela%20and%20Nicaragua%20refused%20to%20take%20any.%20All%20three%20are%20US%20adversaries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHaiti%20accepted%20many%20deportation%20flights%2C%20especially%20after%20a%20surge%20of%20migrants%20from%20the%20Caribbean%20country%20in%20the%20small%20border%20town%20of%20Del%20Rio%2C%20Texas%2C%20in%202021.%20But%20Haiti%20has%20been%20in%20constant%20turmoil%2C%20hampering%20US%20efforts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20late%202022%2C%20more%20than%20half%20a%20million%20people%20have%20come%20to%20the%20U.S.%20under%20the%20policy%2C%20also%20known%20as%20CHNV.%20It%20was%20a%20part%20of%20the%20Biden%20administration's%20approach%20to%20encourage%20people%20to%20come%20through%20new%20legal%20channels%20while%20cracking%20down%20on%20those%20who%20crossed%20the%20border%20illegally.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3