nts%20were%20in%20response%20to%20a%20question%20about%20his%20intention%20to%20run%20Amazon%20like%20%26quot%3Bthe%20world's%20largest%20startup.%26quot%3B%20In%20addition%20to%20the%20manager%20shake-up%2C%20Jassy%20underscored%20the%20need%20to%20build%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-ceo-andy-jassy-calls-on-employees-redefine-company-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eculture%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20speed%20and%20meritocracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmazon%20hasn't%20shared%20how%20exactly%20it%20is%20reducing%20management%20layers.%20Some%20managers%20were%20told%20to%20increase%20their%20number%20of%20direct%20reports%2C%20make%20fewer%20senior%20hires%2C%20and%20cut%20pay%20for%20certain%20employees%2C%20BI%20previously%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20email%20to%20BI%2C%20an%20Amazon%20spokesperson%20said%20the%20company%20has%20now%20completed%20this%20process%2C%20which%20impacted%20a%20%26quot%3Brelatively%20small%20subset%20of%20employees.%26quot%3B%20The%20spokesperson%20added%20that%20Amazon%20combined%20teams%20and%20moved%20managers%20to%20individual%20contributor%20roles%20to%20reach%20its%20goal%2C%20and%20this%20%26quot%3Bdid%20not%20equate%20to%20eliminating%2015%25%20of%20manager%20roles.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20September%202024%2C%20we%20shared%20with%20employees%20that%20we%20set%20a%20goal%20to%20increase%20the%20ratio%20of%20individual%20contributors%20to%20managers%20by%2015%25%20across%20our%20organizations%20because%20it%20was%20the%20right%20time%20to%20bring%20us%20closer%20to%20customers%20and%20reinforce%20our%20culture%20of%20ownership.%20There%20are%20a%20number%20of%20ways%20to%20achieve%20that%20increase.%20We've%20now%20reached%20that%20goal%2C%20which%20we%20believe%20will%20allow%20our%20teams%20to%20move%20even%20faster%20as%20they%20innovate%20for%20customers%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20spokesperson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223e0e4a8b-63de-45a1-82a1-b699e197f791%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMeritocracy%20over%20bureaucracy%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20September%2C%20Amazon%20also%20created%20a%20%26quot%3BNo%20Bureaucracy%26quot%3B%20email%20alias%2C%20where%20employees%20could%20report%20unnecessary%20processes%20that%20needed%20to%20be%20fixed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJassy%20said%20during%20the%20Tuesday%20meeting%20that%20he's%20read%20every%20single%20one%20of%20the%20over%20a%20thousand%20emails%20he's%20received%20so%20far%20and%20that%20the%20company%20has%20made%20more%20than%20375%20changes%20as%20a%20result.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%2C%20as%20a%20team%2C%20committed%20to%20getting%20rid%20of%20the%20bureaucracy%2C%26quot%3B%20Jassy%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20companies%20grow%2C%20it's%20natural%20to%20put%20more%20processes%20in%20place%2C%20Jassy%20added.%20But%20companies%20often%20make%20the%20mistake%20of%20focusing%20too%20much%20on%20adding%20more%20people%20and%20managing%20them%20versus%20improving%20the%20customer%20experience%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20how%20charismatic%20you%20are.%20It's%20not%20whether%20you're%20really%20good%20at%20managing%20up%20or%20managing%20sideways%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20matters%20is%20what%20we%20actually%20get%20done%20for%20customers.%20That%20is%20what%20we%20reward.%20It's%20a%20meritocracy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2257ace073-90a7-4074-8cdb-38c5bc4b8432%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E'It%20is%20your%20company'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EJassy%20also%20urged%20employees%20to%20%26quot%3Bmove%20fast%20and%20act%20like%20owners.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20big%20companies%20tend%20to%20become%20slow%20and%20indecisive.%20This%20is%20a%20particularly%20big%20risk%20for%20Amazon%2C%20given%20the%20intense%20competition%20it%20faces.%20Competitors%20include%20the%20%26quot%3Bmost%20technically%20able%2C%20most%20hungry%26quot%3B%20companies%20in%20the%20world%2C%20including%20startups%20%26quo